-- Hungary Stocks: Richter, Egis, OTP Bank Are Active in Budapest
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-02-22T16:17:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-22/hungary-stocks-richter-egis-otp-bank-are-active-in-budapest.html
Hungary’s benchmark BUX stock index
fell 0.7 percent to 19,055.7 as of the close in Budapest.  The following are among the most active equities in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Egis Gyogyszergyar Nyrt. (EGIS)  , the drugmaker owned by
Laboratoires Servier, declined 2.5 percent to 16,305 forint, the
lowest close since Jan. 17, after the government said it plans
to cut subsidies for medicines.  Gedeon Richter Nyrt. (RICHT)  , the country’s biggest
drugmaker, slid 0.5 percent to 38,000.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, declined
1.2 percent to 3,928 forint. European stocks weakened for a
second day. Hungary’s government sought to cut spending as the
country looks to avert losing European Union grants.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
